# Guild Life Adventures - Environment Variables
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# .env.local is gitignored and never committed.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PARTYKIT (required for "Search Online Games" public lobby browser)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PartyKit provides real-time room listing so players can find public games
# without needing a room code. Free quota is plenty for a small indie game.
#
# Setup steps:
#   1. Install the CLI:  npm install -g partykit   (or use npx)
#   2. Login:            npx partykit login
#   3. Deploy:           npx partykit deploy
#      → You get a URL like: guild-life-adventures.<your-name>.partykit.dev
#   4. Set VITE_PARTYKIT_HOST below (without https://)
#
# For local development:
#   Run:  npx partykit dev
#   Then: VITE_PARTYKIT_HOST=localhost:1999
#
# If not set, the lobby browser is disabled gracefully —
# players can still join via room code or same-browser P2P discovery.
#
VITE_PARTYKIT_HOST=guild-life-adventures.your-username.partykit.dev

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PEERJS (optional — for self-hosted PeerJS server with discovery)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If you self-host a PeerJS server with --allow_discovery, set the URL here.
# Example: npx peerjs --port 9000 --allow_discovery
# VITE_PEERJS_HOST=http://localhost:9000

# For GitHub Actions deployment, add these as repository secrets and reference them in your workflow.
